An Outlier in the Men’s Fashion Pack

Essentials

“Men’s wear is nuanced and layered — less about trends and more of an evolution of ideas,” said Heather Shimokawa, the fashion market director at Vanity Fair, who jets off from New York twice a year to the major fashion capitals to take in the latest men’s collections. “The men’s network is small, familiar and familial. Many of my colleagues I count as close friends. We sort of grew up in the industry together.”

She said a certain item — a 30-inch wheeled suitcase from Rimowa — has made her frequent trips through airports a lot easier. “Few things have transformed my travel experience as meaningfully as my luggage. These Rimowa cases have changed my whole outlook on packing and navigating the airport with luggage.”